notesStmt.note: Parchment guard, a fragment of an earlier manuscript (fourteenth century?) between quire 1 and quire 2

msContents.summary: This is a fifteenth-century manuscript copy of Virgil's Aeneid on paper, written in Italy and dated 22 February 1462. There are many textual corrections, annotations and drawings in a later hand. Bears the inscription "Michael Bone."

support.watermark: Bull head watermark visible on some leaves (e.g. fols 33, 45)

supportDesc.foliation: Unfoliated aside from "41", "84, "101", "121", "151", "161", "179" written in modern pencil, upper right recto. Remnants of older foliation visible on some pages (e.g., "25" on modern folio 26), that have since been trimmed

p.signatures: Regular signatures throughout, lower right recto, the first half of each quire signed in the pattern a1, a2, a3, etc.; some signatures in later quires are trimmed

layoutDesc.layout: One column, 28 lines, very lightly frame ruled, first letter of each line is an initial, set in a column; prickings visible very occasionally in the bottom margin, most prickings are trimmed

decoDesc.decoNote: Red initials throughout, 2-4 lines, with brown penwork; marginal doodles added by a later hand; glossed by a later hand, glosses concentrated in the first half of the manuscript
[83r]Doodle of a heart with an arrow through it being stabbed by an arm with a sword
[85r]Large doodle of knight on horse, with some green color
[107r]Doodle of man in a green coat or robe
[179v]Two doodles of hearts with arrows through them

history.provenance: Red and gold book label inside front cover: "Ex Libris Robert Honeyman IV" with shield design
